    "Polymerase errors during DNA polymerization in the PCR process contribute to the issue (Berden et al., 2022).",
    "Challenges also arise from chimeric reads, which are formed from hybrid sequences originating from different templates during amplification (Haas et al., 2011).",
    "Random errors, unpredictable in nature, can emerge during the PCR process, while systematic PCR errors may be associated with specific primer pairs or conditions.",
    "It's crucial to recognize that sequencing itself introduces errors, with Illumina sequencing posing particular challenges due to its imaging-based nature (Pienaar et al., 2006).",
    "These potential sources of error and bias has led to concerns about the accuracy, reproducibility, and potential contamination in microbiome studies (Gohl et al., 2016)."
